-- The hero sprite is a column of 2 stacked 16x16 tiles (16x32 total)
-- instead of one 8x8 tile -- a single OAM sprite maxes out at 16x16 in this
-- hardware, so a character taller than that has to be composited from
-- several sprites stacked edge-to-edge. Simple blocky humanoid: color 1 =
-- head/hands/feet, color 2 = body/legs. A 4x taller, much more visible
-- character than the original 8px blob (a 3-tile/48px version was tried
-- first but overflowed the ROM's code budget -- each 16x16 tile's pixel
-- data is inlined as one MOV pair per source byte at compile time, and even
-- after consolidating the per-frame attr/position/OAM-write logic into
-- shared functions, 3 tiles didn't fit).
asset PlayerTop: tiles16 hex
